# 💎 Code of Conduct

Welcome to the **Python Learning Repository**!  
Our community values respect, collaboration, and continuous learning.  
This Code of Conduct outlines the expectations for all contributors and participants to ensure a positive and inclusive environment for everyone.

---

## 🌟 Our Pledge

We are committed to providing a welcoming and inspiring environment for people of all backgrounds and skill levels.  
As contributors and maintainers, we pledge to make participation in our community a harassment-free experience for everyone — regardless of:

- Age  
- Gender identity or expression  
- Race or ethnicity  
- Experience level  
- Education or background  
- Religion or political beliefs  

---

## 💬 Our Standards

Examples of positive behavior include:

- Being respectful and kind to others  
- Giving constructive feedback and accepting it gracefully  
- Focusing on what’s best for the community  
- Using inclusive and supportive language  
- Offering help and encouragement to beginners  

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Use of sexualized language or imagery  
- Personal attacks, insults, or trolling  
- Harassment or discrimination of any kind  
- Sharing others’ private information without consent  
- Any conduct that would make others feel unsafe or unwelcome  

---

## ⚖️ Our Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying acceptable behavior and taking appropriate action when participants engage in unacceptable conduct.  
They have the right to remove or reject contributions that violate this Code of Conduct.

---

## 🚫 Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by contacting the repository maintainer:  
**Maintainer:** Sehrish Javed  
**GitHub:** [@sehrishjaved19](https://github.com/sehrishjaved19)  

All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

---

## 💡 Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/), version 2.1.

---

## 🌱 Our Commitment to Growth

We believe learning is most effective in a positive, supportive environment.  
Let’s work together to make this space one where everyone feels encouraged to grow, share knowledge, and succeed.  

**Thank you for being part of this community! 💖**

---

